From: Marcin FM <marcin@lgic.pl>
Subject: [PATCH] Include climits for CHAR_BIT in V8 memcopy

V8's ARM64 SIMD memcpy path uses CHAR_BIT directly. Include the standard
header that defines it instead of relying on a transitive libc++ include.

Upstream issue: https://issues.chromium.org/issues/512749476
---
diff --git a/v8/src/base/memcopy.h b/v8/src/base/memcopy.h
--- a/v8/src/base/memcopy.h
+++ b/v8/src/base/memcopy.h
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@
 #include <stdlib.h>
 
 #include <atomic>
+#include <climits>
 
 #include "include/v8config.h"
 #include "src/base/base-export.h"
